rComments: He's just really cool and interesting. Taking his Buddhism course is an experience you will definitely enjoy.

He's extremely nice and I am impressed with how attentive he is considering he has over 200 students (less than 20 dropped the course starting from by week 7). His class was a little hard in the beginning but after week 5 I was used the readings and it got easier. He is probably the most knowledgeable professor in religion at UTM.
Professor Emmrich is one of the kindest person I ever met at UTM. Amazing professor and a true human being.

Amazing person. Truly a master at his craft. This professor is passionate and cares about providing knowledge. Definitely, a true professor. Course content was entertaining, and enlightening. Definitely take it regardless of what faith you are.

Professor Emmrich is the best professor I have ever had. I've taken his course without any background knowledge. He was very supportive and encouraging. I like that he summaries the material in the beginning of the class and opens up the conversation. Even very complicated term and conceptions are gracefully explained with simple words. SMART & HOT

Professor Emmrich is honestly one of the kindest professors I've ever had! He's  understanding and is really passionate about his material. In all honesty, the marks you get are truly reflective of the amount of effort you put in! As long as you try, you're guaranteed a high mark in the course. (Personal experience: I finished with a 90!)
He is the sweetest man ever. His class was so interesting! I Learned a lot about Buddhism. He definitely knows what he's talking about!
